3:
Yes, Yahweh will comfort Zion; he will comfort all her waste places;\q1 her wilderness he made like Eden, and her desert plains beside the Jordan River valley like the garden of Yahweh;
\q1 joy and gladness will be found in her, thanksgiving, and the sound of singing.


\q1

17:
Awake, awake, stand up, Jerusalem,\q1 you who have drunk out of the hand of Yahweh from the bowl of his anger;
\q1 you who have drunk out of the bowl, down to the dregs from the cup of staggering.
\q1
